It looks like you wrote `+f+`(async () => ...) or returned a Promise. Instead, write the async function inside your effect and call it immediately:

`+f+`(() => {
  async function fetchData() {
    // You can await here
    const response = await MyAPI.getData(someId);
    // ...
  }
